Maven Installation Step by Step

Step 1: prerequisite
Make sure JDK installed and enivronmental variables are configured.

Step 2: Download
Go to the link "https://maven.apache.org/download.cgi" to download the file

Step 3: Installation
Extract/Un zip the downloaded file
(Make sure the Extracted folder location didn't changed)

Step 4: Configuration
Click Windows key+s and search 'environment' Click Edit environment variables (windows 10)
Or Open System Properties
Under the window goto advanced tab and click Environment Variables
Add the 'apache-maven-3.8.4/bin' directory in the PATH environmental variable

Step 5: Test Configuration
Open Command prompt and type mvn -v
It will show the maven version, java version installed on the system.
